messages.textToSpeech:
At this time we are asking patients to go to the emergency department for emergencies only. Access to a COVID-19 test is not an emergency.

Ask me to walk you through the Self Assessment questions to help determine if you need further assessment or testing for COVID-19. You can complete this assessment for yourself, or on behalf of someone else, if they are unable to.

If you have COVID-19 compatible symptoms avoid contact with others and self-isolate at home for at least 10 days.

You can head over to the "BCCDC If You are Sick" page for details on how to stop the spread of germs, what to do if your symptoms get worse and ending self-isolation.
